social_posts.post_text: Great day at the bay, what an amazing event to witness, congrats to everyone who paddled out to pay homage to such an incredible human being @theeddieaikau congrats Luke Shepardson on winning this prestigious title, in between lifeguard duties nonetheless.

Today we celebrated the life & legacy of #JayAdams at #banzaiskatepark Mahalo to everyone who came out and showed aloha. I met Jay in the late 80’s at the Hickam Hanger, he was with @christianhosoi and a bunch of other pros, we were all on the mini ramp, I remember being the only bmx guy there waiting on the deck, and Jay was like you ever gonna take a run or what? I remember him putting his board on the coping and telling me to drop in. Fast forward many years later, we met up again at House of Flys in Waikiki with @sciflyhawaii before one of the Once-A-Month punk shows. I’d see Jay at all the punk shows at night then see him at the skatepark in the mornings. Jay let me ride with him and he got me into some killer skate only spots with him, always grateful for that, Mahalo. Today it was great to see all the groms ripping it up in the bowl with all these legendary skaters. All these guys I looked up to and inspired me when I was a kid are now friends/ohana many years later, these sessions and gatherings mean so much to me now more than ever. So grateful and blessed to share these moments in time with everyone.
Baby Zion got to meet his Uncle @christianhosoi @popshosoi Mahalo always for the prayers and positive Mana.
Secret Ninja Warehouse always has the best people stopping by to get tattooed, who’s next? @noahcyrus

51 today… what a year, got married last year, happy anniversary @leahdarling I love you, moved to the farmhouse off grid, got a puppy named Duke, we had a baby boy Zion and his big sister @iza_lolol was just in town to meet him. Woke up, went surfing, then skatepark to ride and skate, watching @nascar uncle @travispastrana , and spending rest of day with wifey and baby Zion. Life goes by quick so make the best of it. Shoots & mahalos!

Got blessed by the man @markmahoney_ssc I’ve been getting tattooed by Mark since the mid 90’s, getting tattooed by him is what got me into wanting to be a tattooer, the stories, the experiences, his charm and charisma makes the tattoo experience so special. I was blessed to have apprenticed under Mark and the @shamrocksocialclub ohana. Mahalo Mark for everything.

RIP @patcaseybmx I got to watch Pat grow up riding in X-Games @xgames and Vans events @vansbmx66. He came out to Hawai’i and got tattooed at our sister shop @skindeeptattoowaikiki and my friend tattooing him called me and said there was a bmx guy getting tattooed, so I walked over and it was Pat, he was so surprised to see me and confused, he thought I lived on the Big Island. We got to hang out that night and the next morning, he was such a nice kid. I got to see him become a great husband and dad, made it out to the Dream Yard to tattoo him and his ohana and neighbors during the X-Games at his house, Mahalo to @monstermusic you will be missed by our bmx ohana. My thoughts, prayers, love & aloha to you and your ohana @chasecasey @reidcaseybmx #taytumcasey

22 years of being @shamrocksocialclub met some of the most talented tattooers, tattooed the most interesting people, learned a lot about life, and had the best experiences ever. I will always be grateful to @markmahoney_ssc for bringing me into the tattoo world and letting me be a part of something so special. Mahalo and a Hui Hou.

Thank you to everyone who came by, got tattooed, sent us well wishes, and are a part of the Shamrock Social Club family. Times are changing everyday in this world and we are here for it! Thank you for 22 years in one location and bless the future for all! We are beginning our build out of the new spot and cannot wait to open our doors in 2024! To all the Artists. clients, and friends who have walked through our doors we are grateful and humbled. Sending love to everyone in this Holiday season. Onward & upward ☘️
